{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885678045,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b08f3bb001wz7NKE6wVISoeB","messageID":"msg_d7b08e97c0011OobsK1WWSQ9Oe","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-75bd2dbd90a44b48a3aeb076388cd5a2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n8: **Language:** Python  \n9: **Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### Components\n14: \n15: | Component | Location | Responsibility |\n16: |-----------|----------|----------------|\n17: | `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n18: | `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n19: | `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n20: | `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |\n21: \n22: ### Data Flow\n23: \n24: ```\n25: CLI Options ŌåÆ MetadataOptions ŌåÆ PackRuntime.pack()\n26:                                       Ōåō\n27:                      _validate_workspace_structure()\n28:                                       Ōåō\n29:                       _load_or_create_metadata()\n30:                                       Ōåō\n31:                       _apply_option_overrides()\n32:                                       Ōåō\n33:                     _validate_language_compatibility()\n34:                                       Ōåō\n35:                          _process_dependencies()\n36:                                       Ōåō\n37:                          _generate_dockerfile()\n38:                                       Ōåō\n39:                      _update_pack_metadata()\n40:                                       Ōåō\n41:                          _prepare_output_path()\n42:                                       Ōåō\n43:                             Return result\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ## Detailed Implementation\n47: \n48: ### 1. CLI Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n49: \n50: ```python\n51: def pack(\n52:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n53:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n54:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n55:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n56:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n57:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n58:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n59:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n60:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n61: ) -> None:\n62:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating structure and generating metadata.\"\"\"\n63: ```\n64: \n65: **Command behavior:**\n66: - Resolves workspace path relative to current directory if not absolute\n67: - Creates `PackRuntime` instance with verbose flag\n68: - Collects options into a dictionary\n69: - Calls `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n70: - Handles exceptions via `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)`\n71: \n72: ### 2. PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n73: \n74: #### Class Structure\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class PackRuntime:\n78:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n79:         self.verbose = verbose\n80:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: #### Main Method: `pack()`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n87:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\n88: \n89:     Returns:\n90:         Dict containing:\n91:         - agent_name: str\n92:         - workspace_path: str (absolute path)\n93:         - metadata_path: str\n94:         - dockerfile_path: Optional[str]\n95:         - language: str\n96:         - entrypoint: str\n97:         - port: int\n98:     \"\"\"\n99:     with Progress() as progress:\n100:         task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packing workspace...\", total=100)\n101: \n102:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n103:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n104: \n105:         progress.update(task, advance=20)\n106:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n107: \n108:         progress.update(task, advance=20)\n109:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n110: \n111:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n112:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n113: \n114:         progress.update(task, advance=15)\n115:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n116: \n117:         progress.update(task, advance=15)\n118:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n119: \n120:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n121:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n122: \n123:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n124:         output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n125: \n126:     return {\n127:         \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n128:         \"workspace_path\": str(output_path),\n129:         \"metadata_path\": str(output_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n130:         \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n131:         \"language\": metadata.language,\n132:         \"entrypoint\": metadata.entrypoint,\n133:         \"port\": metadata.port,\n134:     }\n135: ```\n136: \n137: #### Helper Methods\n138: \n139: **`_validate_workspace_structure()`**\n140: - Validates `workspace_path` exists and is a directory\n141: - Raises `ValueError` with clear message if not\n142: \n143: **`_load_or_create_metadata()`**\n144: - Attempts to load existing metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n145: - Falls back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if primary missing\n146: - Creates new `AgentMetadata` if no existing file found\n147: - Infers defaults: `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`\n148: \n149: **`_apply_option_overrides()`**\n150: - Merges CLI options into metadata\n151: - Priority: CLI options > existing metadata > defaults\n152: - Creates new `AgentMetadata` instance to ensure validation\n153: \n154: **`_validate_language_compatibility()`**\n155: - Validates Python workspace: requires at least one `*.py` file\n156: - Validates Java workspace: requires `pom.xml` file\n157: - Raises `ValueError` with specific message per language\n158: \n159: **`_process_dependencies()`**\n160: - Python: Validates `requirements.txt` exists, creates if missing with minimal content\n161: - Java: Validates `pom.xml` exists (already checked in compatibility)\n162: \n163: **`_generate_dockerfile()`**\n164: - Skips if `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n165: - Calls language-specific generator based on `metadata.language`\n166: - Returns path to generated Dockerfile or None\n167: \n168: **`_generate_python_dockerfile()`**\n169: - Base image: `python:3.11-slim`\n170: - Workdir: `/app`\n171: - Copy requirements and install\n172: - Copy application code\n173: - Expose port from metadata\n174: - Entrypoint from metadata\n175: \n176: **`_generate_java_dockerfile()`**\n177: - Base image: `openjdk:17-jdk-slim`\n178: - Workdir: `/app`\n179: - Copy `pom.xml` and run Maven build\n180: - Copy JAR from target\n181: - Expose port from metadata\n182: - Entrypoint: `java -jar {jar_name}`\n183: \n184: **`_update_pack_metadata()`**\n185: - Saves metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` using `MetadataService`\n186: - Excludes None fields from output\n187: - Updates dockerfile_path in metadata\n188: \n189: **`_prepare_output_path()`**\n190: - Returns workspace_path if output not specified\n191: - Creates output directory if doesn't exist\n192: - Returns absolute path\n193: \n194: **`_infer_entrypoint()`**\n195: - Python: `python main.py` if `main.py` exists\n196: - Java: `java -jar target/*.jar`\n197: - Default: metadata.entrpoint or raise error\n198: \n199: ### 3. MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n200: \n201: ```python\n202: class MetadataService:\n203:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n204:         self.verbose = verbose\n205:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n206: \n207:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n208:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace with fallback order.\"\"\"\n209:         for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n210:             metadata_path = workspace_path / filename\n211:             if metadata_path.exists():\n212:                 with open(metadata_path, \"r\") as f:\n213:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n214:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n215:         raise FileNotFoundError(\"No metadata file found in workspace\")\n216: \n217:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n218:         \"\"\"Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n219:         metadata_path = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n220:         with open(metadata_path, \"w\") as f:\n221:             yaml.dump(\n222:                 metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n223:                 f,\n224:                 default_flow_style=False,\n225:                 indent=2,\n226:                 sort_keys=False,\n227:             )\n228: \n229:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n230:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure based on language.\"\"\"\n231:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n232:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n233:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n234:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n235:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n236:         return True\n237: \n238:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n239:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\"\"\"\n240:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n241:         if not py_files:\n242:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n243: \n244:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n245:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has pom.xml.\"\"\"\n246:         if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n247:             raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 4. MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n251: \n252: ```python\n253: @dataclass\n254: class MetadataOptions:\n255:     \"\"\"Options for pack command CLI arguments.\"\"\"\n256:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n257:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n258:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n259:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n260:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n261:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n262:     description: Optional[str] = None\n263:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n264:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n265:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n266:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n267:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n268:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n269:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n270:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n271: \n272:     @classmethod\n273:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n274:         \"\"\"Create from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n275:         return cls(\n276:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n277:             language=options.get(\"language\"),\n278:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n279:             port=options.get(\"port\"),\n280:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n281:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n282:             workspace_manager_url=options.get(\"workspace_manager_url\"),\n283:             router_url=options.get(\"router_url\"),\n284:             readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\"),\n285:             readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\"),\n286:         )\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ### 5. AgentMetadata (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n290: \n291: ```python\n292: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n293:     \"\"\"Agent metadata model with validation.\"\"\"\n294:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n295:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n296:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n297:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n298:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n299:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n300:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n301:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n302:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n303:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n304:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n305:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n306:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n307:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n308:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n309:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n310:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n311:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n312:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n313:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n314:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n315:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n316: \n317:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n318:     @classmethod\n319:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n320:         \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n321:         v = v.lower()\n322:         if v not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n323:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Supported: python, java\")\n324:         return v\n325: \n326:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n327:     @classmethod\n328:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n329:         \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n330:         v = v.lower()\n331:         if v not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n332:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Supported: local, cloud\")\n333:         return v\n334: \n335:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n336:     @classmethod\n337:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n338:         \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n339:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n340:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n341:         return v\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ## Error Handling\n345: \n346: ### Error Flow\n347: \n348: ```python\n349: try:\n350:     result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n351:     # Print success with Rich console\n352:     console.print(f\"[green]Ō£ō[/green] Agent packed successfully: {result['agent_name']}\")\n353:     console.print(f\"  Workspace: [cyan]{result['workspace_path']}[/cyan]\")\n354:     console.print(f\"  Metadata: [cyan]{result['metadata_path']}[/cyan]\")\n355:     if result['dockerfile_path']:\n356:         console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: [cyan]{result['dockerfile_path']}[/cyan]\")\n357: except Exception as e:\n358:     _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ### `_handle_error()` Implementation\n362: \n363: ```python\n364: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n365:     \"\"\"Handle command errors with optional traceback.\"\"\"\n366:     console = Console()\n367:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}:[/red] {e}\")\n368:     if verbose:\n369:         import traceback\n370:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n371:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### Common Error Scenarios\n375: \n376: | Error | Condition | Message |\n377: |-------|-----------|---------|\n378: | `ValueError` | Workspace doesn't exist | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n379: | `ValueError` | No Python files | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n380: | `ValueError` | No pom.xml for Java | \"Java workspace requires pom.xml\" |\n381: | `ValueError` | Invalid language | \"Unsupported language: {lang}. Supported: python, java\" |\n382: | `ValueError` | Invalid build mode | \"Unsupported build mode: {mode}. Supported: local, cloud\" |\n383: | `ValueError` | Invalid port | \"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {port}\" |\n384: | `PydanticValidationError` | Invalid metadata type | Validation errors from Pydantic |\n385: \n386: ## CLI Output Format\n387: \n388: ### Success Output\n389: \n390: ```\n391: Ō£ō Agent packed successfully: my-agent\n392:   Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n393:   Metadata: /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n394:   Dockerfile: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Error Output (non-verbose)\n398: \n399: ```\n400: Error pack: No Python files found in workspace\n401: ```\n402: \n403: ### Error Output (verbose)\n404: \n405: ```\n406: Error pack: No Python files found in workspace\n407: Traceback (most recent call last):\n408:   File \"...\", line ..., in pack\n409:     self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path)\n410:   ...\n411: ```\n412: \n413: ## Dependencies\n414: \n415: ### Runtime Dependencies (from `pyproject.toml`)\n416: \n417: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n418: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n419: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing/writing\n420: - `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal output formatting\n421: \n422: ### Optional Dependencies\n423: \n424: - `docker>=6.0.0` - Used by `DockerService` (not in pack command)\n425: \n426: ## Test Coverage\n427: \n428: ### Unit Tests Required\n429: \n430: | Component | Test Cases |\n431: |-----------|------------|\n432: | `PackRuntime.pack()` | - Happy path with valid workspace<br>- Workspace validation failure<br>- Metadata loading fallback<br>- Option override merging<br>- Language-specific validation<br>- Dockerfile generation |\n433: | `_validate_workspace_structure()` | - Existing directory<br>- Non-existent path<br>- File instead of directory |\n434: | `_load_or_create_metadata()` | - Load existing metadata<br>- Fallback to agent.yaml<br>- Fallback to metadata.yaml<br>- Create new metadata<br>- Infer defaults |\n435: | `_apply_option_overrides()` | - Override all fields<br>- Partial override<br>- No override |\n436: | `_validate_language_compatibility()` | - Valid Python workspace<br>- Python workspace with no .py files<br>- Valid Java workspace<br>- Java workspace without pom.xml |\n437: | `_generate_dockerfile()` | - Python local build<br>- Java local build<br>- Cloud build (skip) |\n438: | `MetadataService` | - Load metadata from all filenames<br>- Save metadata with exclude_none<br>- Validate workspace per language |\n439: \n440: ### Integration Tests\n441: \n442: - End-to-end pack command with workspace\n443: - CLI option parsing and passing\n444: - Error handling flow\n445: \n446: ## Security Considerations\n447: \n448: 1. **Path validation**: Ensure workspace path is within expected directory to prevent path traversal\n449: 2. **Dockerfile generation**: Validate port range to prevent invalid container configuration\n450: 3. **Metadata persistence**: Exclude sensitive fields (auth tokens) from saved metadata if not needed\n451: 4. **Command injection**: Validate and sanitize entrypoint command before writing to Dockerfile\n452: \n453: ## Future Enhancements\n454: \n455: 1. Support for additional languages (Node.js, Go, etc.)\n456: 2. Multi-stage Dockerfile generation for optimized images\n457: 3. Dependency analysis to include only required packages\n458: 4. Workspace templates for quick-start\n459: 5. Interactive mode for metadata creation\n460: 6. Workspace validation rules extensible via plugins\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n| `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n| `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n| `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775885678026,"end":1775885678042}}}}
