{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885688734,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0914ef001K2iEgF2QAiXbbH","messageID":"msg_d7b090c09001XN5e02LIBBKXpW","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e1f596d2334a4674a301e2e38e0d667e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD ŌĆö Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` ŌåÆ `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | ŌĆö |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | ŌĆö |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none ŌĆö scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` ŌåÆ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | ŌĆö | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` ŌåÆ `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` ŌåÆ default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` ŌåÆ **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` ŌåÆ **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` ŌåÆ `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) ŌåÆ pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` ŌåÆ `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) ŌåÆ pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` ŌåÆ `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ OWNERS\n131: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e/\n132:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md\n133:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ __init__.py\n134:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ run_e2e.sh\n135:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_test.go\n136:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ echo_agent.yaml\n138:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` ŌåÆ `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic ŌĆ£install CRDs and agent-sandboxŌĆØ; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD ŌĆö Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` ŌåÆ `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | ŌĆö |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | ŌĆö |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none ŌĆö scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` ŌåÆ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | ŌĆö | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775885688713,"end":1775885688732}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885688737,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b091cef001B1s5a7pvKOp926","messageID":"msg_d7b090c09001XN5e02LIBBKXpW","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5ac4dae5ca0044fd9c67e705d2598bc9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the ŌĆ£Agentcube CI WorkflowŌĆØ job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the ŌĆ£Agentcube CI WorkflowŌĆØ job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775885688716,"end":1775885688735}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775885688764,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b091fa0001ry7nbGTxoUCjA4","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b090c09001XN5e02LIBBKXpW","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":24211,"input":1836,"output":168,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":22207}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775885694783,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b09373c001PU5Tonjls37g0M","messageID":"msg_d7b091fd00017qrMyUHFkF5gch","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885817933,"sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0b17870010mh4n0Lrga6PnV","messageID":"msg_d7b091fd00017qrMyUHFkF5gch","sessionID":"ses_284f729caffeQ4drVrs5W3IZew","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-265b09f14bc84787afeaa4101f1148fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions ŌĆö Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe CI/CD system for AgentCube consists of 12 GitHub Actions workflows that automate build verification, testing, linting, code generation checks, and release publishing. These workflows are written in YAML and configured in the `.github/workflows/` directory.\n\n**Module:** `.github/workflows/`  \n**Language:** YAML (GitHub Actions)  \n**Size:** L (Large - 12 workflows)\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Workflow Categories\n\nThe 12 workflows are organized into four functional categories:\n\n| Category | Workflows | Purpose |\n|----------|-----------|---------|\n| **Build & Verify** | `main.yml`, `lint.yml`, `python-lint.yml` | Verify builds and code quality |\n| **Testing** | `e2e.yml`, `python-sdk-tests.yml`, `test-coverage.yml` | Run unit, integration, and E2E tests |\n| **Quality Gates** | `codegen-check.yml`, `copyright-check.yml`, `codespell.yml` | Enforce code quality standards |\n| **Publish & Approvals** | `build-push-release.yml`, `dify-plugin-publish.yml`, `workflows-approve.yml` | Publish artifacts and approve workflows |\n\n### Component Interaction\n\n```\nGitHub Event Triggers\n         Ōåō\n    Path Filters (dorny/paths-filter)\n         Ōåō\n    Workflow Execution\n         Ōåō\n    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    Ōöé   Go    Ōöé   Python   Ōöé  Docker  Ōöé   External   Ōöé\n    Ōöé Actions Ōöé   Actions  Ōöé  Actions Ōöé   Services   Ōöé\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö┤ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö┤ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö┤ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n         Ōåō         Ōåō           Ōåō           Ōåō\n    Artifacts & Reports (Code coverage, test logs, images)\n```\n\n### Workflow Orchestration\n\n#### Path-Filtering Strategy\n\nMost workflows use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` to conditionally execute based on changed files:\n\n```yaml\nfilters:\n  lint:\n    - '**/*.go'\n    - 'go.mod'\n    - 'go.sum'\n    - '.golangci.yml'\n    - '.github/workflows/lint.yml'\n  sdk:\n    - 'sdk-python/**'\n  python:\n    - 'cmd/cli/**'\n    - 'sdk-python/**'\n    - 'example/**'\n    - 'test/**/*.py'\n    - 'pyproject.toml'\n```\n\n#### Workflow Call Reusability\n\nThe `test-coverage.yml` workflow can be invoked as a reusable workflow:\n\n```yaml\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    secrets:\n      CODECOV_TOKEN:\n        required: false\n```\n\n## Detailed Workflow Specifications\n\n### 1. main.yml ŌĆö Agentcube CI Workflow\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Jobs:** `build`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository (`actions/checkout@v4`)\n2. Setup Docker Buildx (`docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`)\n3. Verify Docker installation\n4. Build workload manager image (`make docker-build`)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Single job workflow with sequential steps\n- No matrix strategy\n- Uses self-hosted or GitHub-hosted runner with Docker support\n\n**Data Flow:**\n```\nPR Event ŌåÆ Checkout ŌåÆ Buildx Setup ŌåÆ Docker Build ŌåÆ Success/Failure\n```\n\n### 2. e2e.yml ŌĆö Agentcube E2E Tests\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Jobs:** `e2e-test`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Install Kind v0.30.0 (`helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`)\n3. Set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n4. Setup Go 1.23\n5. Run E2E tests (`make e2e`)\n6. On failure: upload `e2e-logs/` as artifact\n7. Always: run `make e2e-clean`\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Uses Kind cluster for Kubernetes testing\n- Captures logs on failure for debugging\n- Cleans up cluster after test completion\n\n**Data Structures (E2E Test Environment):**\n```yaml\nenvironment:\n  E2E_CLUSTER_NAME: \"agentcube-e2e\"\n  AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE: \"agentcube\"\n  WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT: 8080\n  ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT: 8081\n  API_TOKEN: \"<k8s-service-account-token>\"\n  AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION: \"v0.1.1\"\n```\n\n### 3. lint.yml ŌĆö Go Linting\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Path Filters:** `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n\n**Jobs:** `golangci`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Setup Go 1.24\n4. Run `make lint` (invokes golangci-lint)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Conditional execution based on Go file changes\n- Uses golangci-lint as the linting engine\n- Single job with sequential steps\n\n**API Contract (Make Target):**\n```makefile\nlint:\n\t@echo \"Running golangci-lint...\"\n\tgolangci-lint run ./...\n```\n\n### 4. python-sdk-tests.yml ŌĆö Python SDK Tests\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request`, `merge_group`\n\n**Path Filters:** `sdk-python/**`\n\n**Jobs:** `python-sdk-tests`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Setup Python 3.12\n4. Install pytest\n5. Install SDK in editable mode (`pip install -e .`)\n6. Run pytest (`python -m pytest tests/ -v`)\n\n**Working Directory:** `sdk-python`\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Isolated Python environment for SDK testing\n- Editable install to test local changes\n- Uses pytest as test framework\n\n**API Contract (Test Execution):**\n```bash\ncd sdk-python\npython -m pip install --upgrade pip\npip install pytest\npip install -e .\npython -m pytest tests/ -v\n```\n\n### 5. python-lint.yml ŌĆö Python Linting\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Path Filters:** `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self\n\n**Jobs:** `python_lint`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Setup Python 3.10\n4. Install Ruff\n5. Run Ruff check (`ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Uses Ruff for fast Python linting\n- Configuration in pyproject.toml\n- Lints entire repository for consistency\n\n### 6. test-coverage.yml ŌĆö Go Test Coverage\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call`\n\n**Path Filters:** `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n\n**Jobs:** `coverage`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Free disk space\n4. Setup Go 1.24\n5. Run tests with coverage (`go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`)\n6. Generate step summary\n7. Upload to Codecov (if token provided)\n8. Upload `go-coverage` artifact\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Reusable workflow design\n- Codecov integration for coverage tracking\n- Race detector enabled\n\n**API Contract (Test Command):**\n```bash\ngo test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...\n```\n\n**Coverage Data Structure:**\n```yaml\nartifacts:\n  go-coverage:\n    paths:\n      - coverage.out\n    retention-days: 30\n```\n\n### 7. codegen-check.yml ŌĆö Code Generation Check\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Path Filters:** `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n\n**Jobs:** `codegen-check`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Setup Go 1.24.4\n4. Run `make gen-check`\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Ensures generated code is up-to-date\n- Prevents drift between source and generated files\n\n**API Contract (Make Target):**\n```makefile\ngen-check:\n\t@echo \"Checking generated code...\"\n\tmake gen-all\n\tgit diff --exit-code\n```\n\n### 8. copyright-check.yml ŌĆö Copyright Header Check\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Path Filters:** All files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n\n**Jobs:** `build`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Run paths filter\n3. If changed: Install `moreutils` (`sponge`)\n4. Run `make gen-copyright`\n5. Check git diff exits cleanly (`git diff --exit-code`)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Automates copyright header enforcement\n- Uses sponge for in-place file editing\n\n**API Contract (Make Target):**\n```makefile\ngen-copyright:\n\t@echo \"Generating copyright headers...\"\n\t# Uses tool to add/verify copyright headers\n```\n\n### 9. codespell.yml ŌĆö Spelling Check\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request` targeting `main` or `release-*`\n\n**Jobs:** `codespell`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Backup/remove false-positive files (`pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`)\n3. Install codespell\n4. Run codespell with filters\n5. Restore backed-up files\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Temporary file exclusion for false positives\n- Scans entire codebase\n\n**API Contract (Codespell Command):**\n```bash\npip install codespell\ncodespell --check-filenames \\\n  --skip \"*.pyc,*.dll,*.exe,*.so,*.dylib,*.class,*.jar,*.war,*.ear\" \\\n  --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn \\\n  .\n```\n\n### 10. build-push-release.yml ŌĆö Build and Push Release Images\n\n**Trigger:** `push` to `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*`\n\n**Jobs:** `build-and-push`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Checkout repository\n2. Setup Go 1.24.4\n3. Setup Docker Buildx\n4. Login to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n5. Determine `TAG` from ref (tag name or `latest`)\n6. Set `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n7. Build and push workload manager (`make docker-buildx-push`)\n8. Build and push router (`make docker-buildx-push-router`)\n9. Build and push picod (`make docker-buildx-push-picod`)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Multi-platform image builds\n- Semantic versioning support\n- GitHub Container Registry integration\n\n**Data Structures (Image Tags):**\n```yaml\nenv:\n  TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n  IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n  WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE: workloadmanager:${TAG}\n  ROUTER_IMAGE: agentcube-router:${TAG}\n  PICOD_IMAGE: picod:${TAG}\n```\n\n**Secrets:**\n```yaml\nsecrets:\n  GITHUB_TOKEN:\n    required: true\n```\n\n### 11. dify-plugin-publish.yml ŌĆö Dify Plugin Publish\n\n**Trigger:** `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*`\n\n**Jobs:** `publish`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Download dify-plugin CLI 0.0.6\n2. Install yq\n3. Read `manifest.yaml` using yq\n4. Package plugin\n5. Checkout `author/dify-plugins` with `GH_TOKEN`\n6. Move `.difypkg`\n7. Create branch, commit, push\n8. Create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n\n**Architecture:**\n- External service integration\n- Automated PR creation\n- Plugin packaging and publishing\n\n**API Contract (PR Creation):**\n```bash\ngh pr create \\\n  --base main \\\n  --title \"Plugin: $(yq .name manifest.yaml)\" \\\n  --body \"Automated PR from AgentCube CI/CD\"\n```\n\n**Secrets:**\n```yaml\nsecrets:\n  PLUGIN_ACTION:\n    required: true\n```\n\n### 12. workflows-approve.yml ŌĆö Approve Workflows\n\n**Trigger:** `pull_request_target` with types `labeled`, `synchronize` targeting `main` or `release-**`\n\n**Jobs:** `approve`\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Run GitHub script to list contributor PRs\n2. Check if first-time contributor or has `ok-to-test` label\n3. List workflow runs for SHA with `status: action_required`\n4. Approve each workflow run\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Security-conscious workflow (uses `pull_request_target`)\n- First-time contributor gating\n- Automated approval for trusted contributors\n\n**API Contract (GitHub Script):**\n```javascript\nconst { data: prs } = await github.rest.repos.listPullRequestsAssociatedWithCommit({\n  owner: context.repo.owner,\n  repo: context.repo.repo,\n  commit_sha: context.sha\n});\n\nconst isFirstTime = prs.length <= 1;\nconst hasOkToTest = context.payload.pull_request.labels.some(\n  l => l.name === 'ok-to-test'\n);\n\nif (!isFirstTime || hasOkToTest) {\n  const { data: runs } = await github.rest.actions.listWorkflowRunsForRepo({\n    owner: context.repo.owner,\n    repo: context.repo.repo,\n    head_sha: context.sha,\n    status: 'action_required'\n  });\n\n  for (const run of runs.workflow_runs) {\n    await github.rest.actions.approveWorkflowRun({\n      owner: context.repo.owner,\n      repo: context.repo.repo,\n      run_id: run.id\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Workflow Metadata Structure\n\n```yaml\nname: <workflow-name>\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    tags: [\"v*.*.*\", \"v*.*.*-*\"]\n  workflow_call:\n    secrets:\n      <secret-name>:\n        required: <true|false>\npermissions:\n  contents: read|write\n  pull-requests: read|write\nconcurrency:\n  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n  cancel-in-progress: true|false\njobs:\n  <job-name>:\n    runs-on: <runner-type>\n    steps:\n      - uses: <action>@<version>\n        with:\n          <parameter>: <value>\n        env:\n          <var>: <value>\n        timeout-minutes: <number>\n```\n\n### Path Filter Output Structure\n\n```yaml\noutputs:\n  filter-name:\n    - <changed-file-path>\n    - <another-changed-file-path>\n```\n\n### Artifact Structure\n\n```yaml\nartifacts:\n  <artifact-name>:\n    path: <path-to-artifacts>\n    retention-days: <number>\n    if-no-files-found: warn|error|ignore\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### GitHub Actions API (via `actions/github-script`)\n\n```javascript\n// List workflow runs\nconst runs = await github.rest.actions.listWorkflowRunsForRepo({\n  owner: context.repo.owner,\n  repo: context.repo.repo,\n  head_sha: context.sha,\n  status: 'action_required'\n});\n\n// Approve workflow run\nawait github.rest.actions.approveWorkflowRun({\n  owner: context.repo.owner,\n  repo: context.repo.repo,\n  run_id: run.id\n});\n\n// List PRs for commit\nconst prs = await github.rest.repos.listPullRequestsAssociatedWithCommit({\n  owner: context.repo.owner,\n  repo: context.repo.repo,\n  commit_sha: context.sha\n});\n```\n\n### Docker Buildx API\n\n```yaml\n- uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n  with:\n    driver-opts: |\n      image=moby/buildkit:latest\n    platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n```\n\n### Docker Login API\n\n```yaml\n- uses: docker/login-action@v3\n  with:\n    registry: ghcr.io\n    username: ${{ github.actor }}\n    password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n```\n\n### Codecov Upload API\n\n```yaml\n- uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n  with:\n    files: coverage.out\n    flags: unittests\n    name: codecov-umbrella\n    fail_ci_if_error: false\n```\n\n### Kind Cluster API\n\n```yaml\n- uses: helm/kind-action@v1\n  with:\n    cluster_name: agentcube-e2e\n    config: test/e2e/kind-config.yaml\n    version: v0.30.0\n    install_only: true\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Workflow-Level Error Handling\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  example:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    continue-on-error: false\n    steps:\n      - id: setup\n        continue-on-error: true\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n      - name: Check setup\n        if: steps.setup.outcome == 'failure'\n        run: echo \"Go setup failed, using fallback\"\n```\n\n### Step-Level Error Handling\n\n```yaml\n- name: Run tests\n  id: test\n  run: make test\n- name: Upload logs on failure\n  if: failure()\n  uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n  with:\n    name: test-logs\n    path: logs/\n- name: Always cleanup\n  if: always()\n  run: make clean\n```\n\n### Common Error Scenarios\n\n| Error | Condition | Handling |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| `Go setup failed` | `actions/setup-go@v5` fails | Log error, fail workflow |\n| `Docker build failed` | `make docker-build` fails | Upload build logs, fail job |\n| `Kind cluster creation failed` | `kind create cluster` fails | Upload Kind logs, always cleanup |\n| `Test timeout` | Test exceeds timeout | Upload test artifacts, fail job |\n| `Path filter error` | `dorny/paths-filter` fails | Continue with default filter |\n| `Secret missing` | Required secret not provided | Fail workflow with clear message |\n| `Artifact upload failed` | Upload exceeds limits | Log warning, continue |\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n```yaml\n- name: Install dependencies\n  uses: nick-invision/retry@v2\n  with:\n    timeout_minutes: 10\n    max_attempts: 3\n    retry_on: error\n    command: pip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\n### Timeout Configuration\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  build:\n    timeout-minutes: 30\n    steps:\n      - name: Long running step\n        timeout-minutes: 10\n        run: make test\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Workflow Testing Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Implementation |\n|-------|-------------|----------------|\n| **Unit** | Individual workflow steps | `act` local testing |\n| **Integration** | Multi-step workflow execution | Test PRs in fork |\n| **E2E** | Full CI/CD pipeline | Release branch testing |\n\n### Local Testing with `act`\n\n```bash\n# Install act\nbrew install act\n\n# Run specific workflow\nact -W .github/workflows/main.yml -j build\n\n# Run with secrets\nact -W .github/workflows/build-push-release.yml --secret GITHUB_TOKEN=$TOKEN\n\n# Dry run\nact -n -W .github/workflows/lint.yml\n```\n\n### Workflow Testing Checklist\n\n- [ ] Workflow triggers correctly on expected events\n- [ ] Path filters match correct files\n- [ ] Jobs execute in correct order\n- [ ] Secrets are properly injected\n- [ ] Artifacts are uploaded correctly\n- [ ] Error handling works as expected\n- [ ] Timeout values are appropriate\n- [ ] Permissions are correctly scoped\n\n### Test Data Structure\n\n```yaml\ntest-scenarios:\n  - name: \"Main workflow on PR\"\n    trigger:\n      event: pull_request\n      branch: main\n    expected:\n      - job: build\n        status: success\n  - name: \"Lint on Go changes\"\n    trigger:\n      event: pull_request\n      files:\n        - pkg/server/server.go\n        - go.mod\n    expected:\n      - job: golangci\n        status: success\n  - name: \"E2E on PR\"\n    trigger:\n      event: pull_request\n      branch: main\n    expected:\n      - job: e2e-test\n        status: success\n        artifacts:\n          - e2e-logs (if failed)\n```\n\n### Coverage Metrics\n\n| Workflow | Coverage Target | Current |\n|----------|----------------|---------|\n| Go unit tests | 80% | TBD |\n| Python SDK tests | 75% | TBD |\n| E2E tests | 90% | TBD |\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Secret Management\n\n```yaml\nsecrets:\n  GITHUB_TOKEN:\n    description: \"GitHub token for registry access\"\n    required: true\n  CODECOV_TOKEN:\n    description: \"Codecov token for coverage upload\"\n    required: false\n  PLUGIN_ACTION:\n    description: \"GitHub token for dify-plugin PR creation\"\n    required: true\n```\n\n### Token Permissions\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n  pull-requests: write\n  actions: write\n  packages: write\n  id-token: write\n```\n\n### Workflow Security Best Practices\n\n1. **Use `pull_request_target` for untrusted code**: The `workflows-approve.yml` workflow uses `pull_request_target` to run with repository permissions on untrusted PRs.\n\n2. **Pin action versions**: All actions use major version pins (e.g., `@v4`) to prevent unexpected breaking changes.\n\n3. **Scope permissions**: Minimum required permissions are granted to each workflow.\n\n4. **Secret masking**: Secrets are automatically masked in logs.\n\n5. **Third-party actions**: Use trusted actions from verified publishers.\n\n6. **Dependency pinning**: Go and Python versions are pinned to specific versions for reproducibility.\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\n### Caching Strategies\n\n```yaml\n- name: Cache Go modules\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: |\n      ~/.cache/go-build\n      ~/go/pkg/mod\n    key: ${{ runner.os }}-go-${{ hashFiles('**/go.sum') }}\n    restore-keys: |\n      ${{ runner.os }}-go-\n\n- name: Cache Python packages\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: ~/.cache/pip\n    key: ${{ runner.os }}-pip-${{ hashFiles('**/requirements.txt') }}\n    restore-keys: |\n      ${{ runner.os }}-pip-\n```\n\n### Parallel Job Execution\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  test:\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest]\n        go-version: [1.23, 1.24]\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: ${{ matrix.go-version }}\n```\n\n### Workflow Concurrency\n\n```yaml\nconcurrency:\n  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n  cancel-in-progress: true\n```\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Workflow Status Metrics\n\n- Success rate per workflow\n- Average execution time\n- Failure frequency by step\n- Artifact upload success rate\n\n### Logging Strategy\n\n```yaml\n- name: Enable debug logging\n  run: |\n    echo \"ACTIONS_STEP_DEBUG=true\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n    echo \"ACTIONS_RUNNER_DEBUG=true\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n```\n\n### Step Summaries\n\n```yaml\n- name: Generate summary\n  if: always()\n  run: |\n    echo \"## Test Results\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n    echo \"- Total: ${{ steps.test.outputs.total }}\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n    echo \"- Passed: ${{ steps.test.outputs.passed }}\" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Action Versions\n\n| Action | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `actions/checkout` | v4 | Repository checkout |\n| `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go environment setup |\n| `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python environment setup |\n| `actions/cache` | v4 | Dependency caching |\n| `actions/upload-artifact` | v4 | Artifact upload |\n| `actions/download-artifact` | v4 | Artifact download |\n| `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker Buildx setup |\n| `docker/login-action` | v3 | Docker registry login |\n| `docker/build-push-action` | v5 | Multi-platform builds |\n| `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster setup |\n| `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage reporting |\n| `dorny/paths-filter` | v3 | Path filtering |\n| `github-script` | v7 | GitHub API scripting |\n\n### System Requirements\n\n| Component | Version |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Go | 1.23 - 1.25 |\n| Python | 3.10 - 3.12 |\n| Docker | Latest |\n| Kind | v0.30.0 |\n| kubectl | Latest |\n| Helm | Latest |\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Workflow composition**: Create reusable workflow components for common patterns\n2. **Advanced caching**: Implement cache warming and pre-fetching strategies\n3. **Self-hosted runners**: Add self-hosted runners for faster builds\n4. **Matrix expansion**: Expand matrix testing to include more OS/architecture combinations\n5. **Slack notifications**: Add Slack notifications for workflow failures\n6. **Dependabot integration**: Automate dependency updates\n7. **Security scanning**: Add container security scanning (e.g., Trivy, Snyk)\n8. **Performance profiling**: Add workflow performance profiling and optimization\n9. **Custom actions**: Create custom actions for common operations\n10. **Workflow templates**: Create workflow templates for new features\n\n## Appendix A: Workflow Reference Matrix\n\n| Workflow | File | Triggers | Jobs | Runtime (est.) |\n|----------|------|----------|------|----------------|\n| Build | `main.yml` | PR to main, release-* | build | 5 min |\n| E2E | `e2e.yml` | PR to main, release-* | e2e-test | 15 min |\n| Go Lint | `lint.yml` | PR to main, release-* | golangci | 3 min |\n| Python SDK Tests | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | PR, merge_group | python-sdk-tests | 5 min |\n| Python Lint | `python-lint.yml` | PR to main, release-* | python_lint | 2 min |\n| Coverage | `test-coverage.yml` | PR, merge_group, call | coverage | 10 min |\n| Codegen Check | `codegen-check.yml` | PR to main, release-* | codegen-check | 4 min |\n| Copyright Check | `copyright-check.yml` | PR to main, release-* | build | 2 min |\n| Codespell | `codespell.yml` | PR to main, release-* | codespell | 3 min |\n| Release Build | `build-push-release.yml` | Push to main, tags | build-and-push | 20 min |\n| Dify Plugin | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Push dify-plugin/v* | publish | 5 min |\n| Approve Workflows | `workflows-approve.yml` | PR labeled, sync | approve | 2 min |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775885817810,"end":1775885817928}}}}
